{
  "stem": "20021.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And most people took it not a big deal.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But I had this premonition, you know.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And, indeed, because I left when I left, it was so easy.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Nobody suspected at that point.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Nobody heard of any Jew pretending to be a Gentile.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was unheard of yet.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Later it became often very popular and everybody was suspected of doing that, you see.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "When my parents left, my mother and my brother did that three months later, but they left after the third action, after the third resettlement so no Jews were left subsequently, you know.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So everybody suspected and word spread around that many Jews are trying to save themselves by tearing off the yellow star and simply pretending that they're not Jews.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So having left when I left made it so much easier for me.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So that was June 22, I remember as the day, Saturday.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I went to the railroad station.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What struck me really at the railroad station was a bunch of people trying to enter the trains and there was not enough place for everybody, so there was a big crowd pushing into that small door and everything.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And suddenly, German soldiers are coming and beating up everybody else.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that kind of made me feel safe.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I suddenly thought that the Poles are, you know, being treated like-- like-- like, you know, dog, you know.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I kind of felt-- I don't know why, that gave me security here I'm running for my life and if somebody uncovers me, I can be-- but I felt that I'm not only-- the only one.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In a way, everybody is sort of running away from the Germans or being hit or beaten or so forth, you know.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
